      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;summary&#34;&gt;Summary&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this session, we explore the FAIR principles (Findability, Accessibility, Interoperability, and Reuse) for data management. Topics include open data, archiving and publishing practices, compliance with data protection regulations, and techniques for discovering and accessing data.&lt;/p&gt;
